      • formatTag

        @Nonnull
protected String formatTag()
        Combines various data to form a single string which represents the statement's tag.

        A sane default is provided. If you have multiple log streams going into a single output channel, you may want to add additional identifier information to the tag.

      • log

        public abstract void log(Logger.Level level,
                         String tag,
                         String message,
                         @Nullable
                         Throwable exception)
        Write a log message to its destination. Called for all level-specific methods by default.
        Parameters:
        level - At which the message was reported
        tag - Used to identify the source of the message. See formatTag().
        message - That was logged. If an exception was logged, the message will already contain the exception's information.
        exception - null if no exception was reported
